attributes.purpose: “Black Monday” Scenario - Attack on Oil Pipeline Pumps::::Russia’s largeness in natural gas and oil exporter by volume has impending economic downturn, causing rise in unsteadiness and leading to malicious cyberattacks to gain more control in NG and oil export.::::There is a cyberattack on Saudi Aramco Riyadh & Yanbu Baiji and SPC refineries: 1) Reports false flow rates, pressure, temperature. 2) Russia offers world‐class cyber security services to all three countries, but installs backdoor measures.::::Short term effects show yield of oil decrease by 6.2M b/d, with overall 10% decrease in global oil market for 3 years and price of oil skyrockets.::::Long term has covert cyber control over OPEC control systems.

attributes.purpose: There are three major types of pipelines along the oil transportation route: 1) gathering systems, 2) crude oil pipeline systems, and 3) refined products pipeline systems. ::::Gathering pipeline systems gather crude oil from production wells. This can be siphoned from wells on land, offshore drilling platforms, overseas tankers, and from the storage and treatment tanks. ::::Crude oil pipeline systems transport the crude oil from the gathering systems/pipelines to the refineries. Crude oil systems can be tens to hundreds of miles in length and cross state and continental borders. ::::The refined products pipeline systems transport refined products such as gasoline, kerosene, and many industrial feedstock petrochemicals from refineries to the end user or to storage and distribution terminals. Refined products pipelines can extend tens to thousands of miles and cross state and continental borders.
